. Everything's better with a pretty diagram
The blog post contains a diagram
The blog post explains that DNS resolves www.google.com to another hostname or IP address
The diagram shows that the request is reaching the server IP on port HTTPS 443
The diagram shows that the traffic is encrypted using HTTPS/SSL certificate
The diagram shows that the request is answered by a web server serving the page
The diagram shows that the request is distributed by the load-balancer to a web server
The diagram shows that request is passing through the firewall that accepts traffic on port TCP/443

